def V(phi): 
    return 4*nu* ( -np.cos(phi) + 0.5 * lamb**2 * np.sin(phi)**2 )
def dV(phi):
    return -4*nu* ( np.sin(phi) + 0.5 * lamb**2 * np.sin(2*phi) )

def extract_data(filename, col):
    infile = open(filename,'r')
    lines = infile.readlines()
    field_values = [float(line.split()[col]) for line in lines[1:]]
    infile.close()
    return field_values

def sim_location(sim):
    """ sim = simulation number """
    return '/gpfs/dpirvu/bubble_correlations/lamb{:.1f}'.format(lamb)+'_t'+str(nTime)+'_x'+str(nLat)+'_sim'+str(sim)+'_fields.dat'

def all_real_space_data():
    all_rsp_data = []
    for sim in range(nSims):
        if sim == nSims // 2:
            print('Halfway through.')
#        print('sim: ', sim, ' ongoing')
        sims_tableau = []
        for col in range(nCols):
            simulation = extract_data(sim_location(sim), col)
            simulation = np.reshape(simulation,(nTime, nLat))
            sims_tableau.append(simulation)
        all_rsp_data.append(sims_tableau)
    return(all_rsp_data)

def masked_field_slice(field_slice, threshold):
    mask = [1 if phi_x >= threshold else 0 for phi_x in field_slice]
    masked_field_slice = mask*field_slice
    return masked_field_slice, np.count_nonzero(masked_field_slice)

def add_mask(field_slice, threshold):
    mask = [0 if -threshold <= field_slice[i] <= threshold else 1 for i in range(len(field_slice))]
    return field_slice * mask

def make_mask(simulation, threshold):
    mask = np.ones((nTime, nLat))
    for j in range(nTime):
        for i in range(nLat):
            if -threshold <= simulation[j, i] <= threshold:
                mask[j, i] = 0
    return mask

def plot_masked_field(simulation, threshold):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5,4))
    masked_field = [add_mask(field_slice, threshold) for field_slice in simulation]
    im = ax.imshow(masked_field, aspect='auto', interpolation='none', origin='lower')#, extent=[0, dx*nLat, 0, dtout*nTime]) 
    clb = plt.colorbar(im, ax = ax)
    ax.set(xlabel = r'$x$', ylabel=r'$t$')
    plt.show()
    return

Power Spectrum¶

In [10]:
field_spectrum = [paper_norm / ((dk*k)**2 + m2eff)**0.25 for k in range(nyq)]
phi_x = np.fft.irfft(field_spectrum, nLat) + phi_initial
phi_k = np.fft.rfft(phi_x, nLat)

momentum_spectrum = [paper_norm * ((dk*k)**2 + m2eff)**0.25 for k in range(nyq)]
dt_phi_x = np.fft.irfft(momentum_spectrum, nLat) + dt_phi_initial
dt_phi_k = np.fft.rfft(dt_phi_x, nLat)

def power_spectrum(col, k):
    if col == 0:
        return phi_k[k] * np.conj(phi_k[k])
    elif col == 1:
        return dt_phi_k[k] * np.conj(dt_phi_k[k])
    
def data_pspec_from_rspec(col, sim, k):
    timeslice = random.randrange(nTime)
    field_slice = all_real_data[sim][col][timeslice]
    fft_field_slice = np.fft.irfft(field_slice, nLat)
    return fft_field_slice[k] * np.conj(fft_field_slice[k])

def data_pspec_from_rspec_sim_averaged(col, k):
    return np.mean([data_pspec_from_rspec(col, sim, k).real for sim in all_non_decaying_sims])

def power_spectrum_theoretical_vs_data(col):
    plt.figure(figsize=(7, 5))
    plt.plot(dk*np.arange(1, spec), [data_pspec_from_rspec_sim_averaged(col, k) for k in range(1, spec)], 'go')
    plt.plot(dk*np.arange(1, spec), [power_spectrum(col, k).real for k in range(1, spec)], 'r--')
    plt.xlabel(r'$k$'); plt.ylabel(r'Power Spectrum'); plt.grid(); plt.show()
    return

Peak-Peak Correlator¶

In [12]:
def data_stat(sim_selection, smoothing_scale):
    data = [smoothen(all_real_data[sim][0][random.randrange(nTime)], smoothing_scale)[random.randrange(nLat)] for sim in sim_selection]
    return stat.stdev(data), np.mean(data)

def find_peak_positions(field_slice, peak_threshold):
    """ Finds x coordinate of peaks in masked field with mask applied at threshold. """
    peak_coord = scs.find_peaks(field_slice, height = peak_threshold)[0].tolist()
    if field_slice[-1] > peak_threshold and field_slice[0] > peak_threshold and field_slice[-1] != field_slice[0]:
        if field_slice[0] > field_slice[-1] and field_slice[0] > field_slice[1]:
            peak_coord.append(0)
        elif field_slice[0] < field_slice[-1] and field_slice[-1] > field_slice[-2]:
            peak_coord.append(len(field_slice)-1) # this minds potential boundary discontinuities
    return peak_coord

def find_max_peak(field_slice):
    peak_coord = scs.find_peaks(field_slice)[0].tolist()
    if field_slice[0] > field_slice[-1] and field_slice[0] > field_slice[1]:
        peak_coord.append(0)
    if field_slice[-1] > field_slice[0] and field_slice[-1] > field_slice[-2]:
        peak_coord.append(len(field_slice)-1)
    peak_heights = [field_slice[coord] for coord in peak_coord]
    return field_slice.tolist().index(np.max(peak_heights)), np.max(peak_heights), peak_coord, peak_heights

def smoothen(field_slice, sigma):
    pbc = [j-1 if j < nLat/2+1 else nLat-j+1 for j in range(1, nLat+1)]
    window = [np.exp(- 0.5 * (i*dx/sigma)**2) / np.sqrt(2*np.pi) / sigma for i in pbc]
    real_filter = np.fft.rfft(window / sum(window), len(field_slice))

    fft_field_slice = np.fft.rfft(field_slice, len(field_slice))
    smooth_fft_field_slice = [real_filter[k] * fft_field_slice[k] for k in range(len(fft_field_slice))]
    return np.fft.irfft(smooth_fft_field_slice, len(field_slice))

def nu2phi(x):
    return x*moment0+phi_initial
def phi2nu(x):
    return (x-phi_initial)/moment0

def peak_number_density_est(sim_selection, smoothing_scale, peak_threshold):
    all_field_slices = [all_real_data[sim][0][random.randrange(nTime)] for sim in sim_selection]
    smooth_field_slice = [smoothen(slice, smoothing_scale) for slice in all_field_slices]
    peak_coordinates = [find_peak_positions(field_slice, peak_threshold) for field_slice in smooth_field_slice]
    N_gal = sum([len(coords) for coords in peak_coordinates])
    return N_gal / len(smooth_field_slice[0]) / len(sim_selection)

def analytic_peak_number_density(peak_threshold_nu):
    thr = peak_threshold_nu
    return 0.0163491+np.exp(-0.5*thr**2)*(0.00798842+0.00798842*ssp.erf(0.395992*thr))-0.0163491*ssp.erf(0.810438*thr)

def correlators(sim_selection, smoothing_scale, th, R):
    r_correlator = 0.
    for sim in sim_selection:
        t = random.randrange(nTime)
        field_slice = smoothen(all_real_data[sim][0][t], smoothing_scale)
        peak_coordinates = find_peak_positions(field_slice, th)
        N_gal = len(peak_coordinates)
        if N_gal != 0:
            peak_list = [i-nLat if i >= nLat else i for i in np.asarray(peak_coordinates)+R]
            rivolo_check = sum([1. for i in peak_list if i in peak_coordinates])
            r_correlator += rivolo_check * len(field_slice) / N_gal**2
    return r_correlator / len(sim_selection) - 1.

def time_limits_of_bubble(sim, bubble_limit):
    filter_size = 1 / (dk * 5)
    simulation = all_real_data[sim][0]
    for t in range(len(simulation)):
        right_phi_x = 0.
        field_slice = smoothen(simulation[t], filter_size)
        for phi_x in field_slice:
            if phi_x >= right_phi_at_V_max.x: #2*phi_initial:
                right_phi_x += 1.
        if (t == nTime-1 or right_phi_x >= nLat * bubble_limit):
            t_max = t
            t_min = t_max - bubble_limit * nTime
            if t_min < 0: t_min = 0
            return int(t_min), int(t_max)

def time_of_bubble_start(sim, bubble_limit):
    t_max = time_limits_of_bubble(sim, bubble_limit)[-1]
    list = []
    filter_size = 1 / (dk * 5)
    simulation = all_real_data[sim][0]
    for t in range(t_max):
        right_phi_x = 0.
        field_slice = smoothen(simulation[t], filter_size)
        for phi_x in field_slice:
            if phi_x >= right_phi_at_V_max.x:
                right_phi_x += 1.
        if right_phi_x <= nLat * 0.005:
            list.append(t)
        else:
            list.append(0)
    return max(list)

def triage1(sim_selection):
    print('Before: ', len(sim_selection))
    for sim in sim_selection:
        simulation = all_real_data[sim][0]
        filter_size = 1. / ( dk * 5. )
        light_cone = filter_size * dtout / dx # distance travelled by light in x axis within one time step
        coords = np.empty((nTime, 0)).tolist()
        for t in range(nTime):
            field_slice = smoothen(simulation[t].tolist(), filter_size)
            coords[t] = [x for x in range(nLat) if field_slice[x] >= 1.8 * phi_initial]
            if (t > 0 and len(coords[t]) > 1 and len(coords[t-1]) > 1):
                if (max(coords[t]) > max(coords[t-1]) + light_cone or min(coords[t]) < min(coords[t-1]) - light_cone):
                    if not (max(coords[t]) == nLat-1 and min(coords[t]) == 0):
                        sim_selection.remove(sim)
    print('After: ', len(sim_selection))
    return sim_selection

def triage2(sim_selection):
    print('Before: ', len(sim_selection))
    filter_size = 1. / ( dk * 5. )
    bubble_limit = 0.2
    for sim in sim_selection:
        t_min, t_max = time_limits_of_bubble(sim, bubble_limit)
        if t_max != nTime-1:
            peak_list = []
            for t in np.arange(t_min, t_max+1):
                field_slice = smoothen(all_real_data[sim][0][t], filter_size)
                bubble_position_at_t = [x for x in range(len(field_slice)) if field_slice[x] > 1.8*phi_initial]
                if len(bubble_position_at_t) > 0:
                    peak_list.append(int(np.mean(bubble_position_at_t)))
            if peak_list != []:
                if stat.stdev(peak_list) < nLat*0.025:
                    sim_selection.remove(sim)
    print('After: ', len(sim_selection))
    return sim_selection

def plot_chosen_field_slices(sim, sigma, t_min, t_max):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20,4))
    gs = gridspec.GridSpec(1, 2) 
    ax = [[],[]]
    ax[0] = plt.subplot(gs[0])
    ax[1] = plt.subplot(gs[1])

    field_simulation = all_real_data[sim][0]
    signal = np.asarray(field_simulation[t_min])
    clean_signal = smoothen(signal, sigma)
    noise = signal - clean_signal

    ax[0].plot(np.arange(nLat), signal)
    ax[0].plot(np.arange(nLat), clean_signal,'r', label='t = '+str(t_min))
    ax[0].plot(np.arange(nLat), noise,'g.')
    ax[0].legend(); ax[0].grid()

    signal = np.asarray(field_simulation[t_max])
    clean_signal = smoothen(field_simulation[t_max], sigma)
    noise = signal - clean_signal

    ax[1].plot(np.arange(nLat), signal)
    ax[1].plot(np.arange(nLat), clean_signal,'r', label='t = '+str(t_max))
    ax[1].plot(np.arange(nLat), noise,'g.')
    ax[1].legend(); ax[1].grid(); plt.show()
    return

def plot_slice(field_slice, sigma):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
    plt.plot(np.arange(len(field_slice)), field_slice)
    field_slice_sm = smoothen(field_slice, sigma)
    plt.plot(np.arange(len(field_slice_sm)), field_slice_sm, 'b-')
    coord, height, _, _ = find_max_peak(field_slice_sm)
    plt.plot(coord, height, 'bo', label = 'max = {:.2f}'.format(height))
    plt.xlabel(r'$x$'); plt.grid(); plt.legend(); plt.show()
    return

def plot_simulation(sim, sigma, t_min, t_max):

def plot_surviving_fraction(sim, sigma, t_min, t_max, threshold):
    plt.figure(figsize=(7, 5))
    simulation = all_real_data[sim][0]
    time_list = np.arange(len(simulation)).tolist()

    plt.plot(np.asarray(time_list), fraction, 'ko-', ms=3)

    plt.plot(time_list.index(t_max), fraction[time_list.index(t_max)], 'yo', label='t = '+str(time_list.index(t_max)))

    smooth_count = [masked_field_slice(smoothen(simulation[timeslice], sigma), threshold)[-1] for timeslice in range(len(simulation))]
    smooth_fraction = [c/nLat for c in smooth_count]
    plt.plot(np.asarray(time_list), smooth_fraction, color='dimgray', marker='o', ls='-', ms=3)
    plt.plot(time_list.index(t_min), smooth_fraction[time_list.index(t_min)], 'ro')
    plt.plot(time_list.index(t_max), smooth_fraction[time_list.index(t_max)], 'yo')
    plt.ylabel(r'Fraction above threshold = {:.2f}'.format(threshold)); plt.xlabel(r'$t$')
    plt.legend(); plt.grid(); plt.show()
    return

def find_average_bubble_profile(trajectory):
    field_list_in_reverse = [field_in_simulation[::-1] for field_in_simulation in trajectory[0]]
    momentum_list_in_reverse = [field_in_simulation[::-1] for field_in_simulation in trajectory[1]]

    xerr = np.nanstd(np.array(list(zip_longest(*field_list_in_reverse)), dtype=float), axis=1, ddof=1)
    xerr = [x for x in xerr if str(x) != 'nan'][::-1]
    average_field = np.nanmean(np.array(list(zip_longest(*field_list_in_reverse)), dtype=float), axis=1)[:len(xerr)][::-1]

    yerr = np.nanstd(np.array(list(zip_longest(*momentum_list_in_reverse)), dtype=float), axis=1, ddof=1)
    yerr = [y for y in yerr if str(y) != 'nan'][::-1]
    average_momentum = np.nanmean(np.array(list(zip_longest(*momentum_list_in_reverse)), dtype=float), axis=1)[:len(yerr)][::-1]
    return average_field, average_momentum, xerr, yerr

def trajectory_of_max(sim_selection, bubble_limit, sigma):
    light_cone = sigma * dtout / dx # distance travelled by light in x axis within one time step
    fld, mnt = [], []
    for sim in sim_selection:
        t_max = time_limits_of_bubble(sim, bubble_limit)[-1]
        t_min = time_of_bubble_start(sim, bubble_limit)
        time_list = np.arange(t_min, t_max+1)

        if t_max != nTime - 1:
            field_simulation_sm = [smoothen(all_real_data[sim][0][t], sigma) for t in time_list[::-1]]
            momentum_simulation_sm = [smoothen(all_real_data[sim][1][t], sigma) for t in time_list[::-1]]

            # t = t_max case:
            target_peak = find_max_peak(field_simulation_sm[0])[0]
            peak_field_traj = [field_simulation_sm[0][target_peak]]
            peak_momentum_traj = [momentum_simulation_sm[0][target_peak]]

            multiplier = 1.
            for t in range(1, len(time_list)):
                # produce the future causal lightcone for the peak propagation
                possible_peaks = []
                distance_to_next_peak = light_cone
                left_ray = target_peak - light_cone * multiplier
                right_ray = target_peak + light_cone * multiplier

                peak_coords_on_slice = find_peak_positions(field_simulation_sm[t], phi_initial)
                for peak in peak_coords_on_slice:
                    if ((left_ray <= peak <= right_ray) or 
                        (left_ray < 0 and left_ray <= peak - nLat <= right_ray) or 
                        (right_ray >= nLat and left_ray <= peak + nLat <= right_ray)):
                        if np.abs(target_peak - peak) < distance_to_next_peak:
                            distance_to_next_peak = np.abs(target_peak - peak)
                            possible_peaks.append(peak)
                if possible_peaks != []:
                    target_peak = possible_peaks[-1]
#                    if field_simulation_sm[t][target_peak] > phi_initial + (right_phi_at_V_max.x - phi_initial) / 2.:
                    peak_field_traj.append(field_simulation_sm[t][target_peak])
                    peak_momentum_traj.append(momentum_simulation_sm[t][target_peak])
                    multiplier = 1.
#                    else:
#                        break
                else:
                    multiplier += 1. # if we do find a peak within the lightcone, reset multiplier
            fld.append(peak_field_traj[::-1])
            mnt.append(peak_momentum_traj[::-1])
    return fld, mnt

def plot_trajectory_of_max(boolean, sim_selection, bubble_limit, sigma):

def truncateNum(num, decimal_places):
    StrNum = str(num)
    p = StrNum.find(".") + 1 + decimal_places
    return ( StrNum[0:p] )

def cut_out_bubble(sim, window_size, bubble_limit):
    t_min, t_max = time_limits_of_bubble(sim, bubble_limit)#[-1]
#    t_min = time_of_bubble_start(sim, bubble_limit)
    time_list = np.arange(t_min, t_max+1)[::-1]
    peak_list = []
    if t_max != nTime-1:
        filter_size = 1 / (dk * 5)
        for t in time_list:
            field_slice = smoothen(all_real_data[sim][0][t], filter_size)
            bubble_position_at_t = [x for x in range(len(field_slice)) if field_slice[x] > 1.8*phi_initial]
            if len(bubble_position_at_t) > 0:
                peak_list.append(int(np.mean(bubble_position_at_t)))
        if peak_list != []:
            target_peak = int(np.mean(peak_list))
            if stat.stdev(peak_list) < nLat*0.025:
                left = target_peak - window_size
                right = target_peak + window_size
                # periodic boundary conditions
                if left >= 0 and right < nLat: 
                    coord_list = np.arange(nLat)[left:right]
                elif left < 0 and right < nLat: 
                    coord_list = np.arange(nLat)[left+nLat:].tolist() + np.arange(nLat)[:right].tolist()
                elif left >= 0 and right >= nLat: 
                    coord_list = np.arange(nLat)[left:].tolist() + np.arange(nLat)[:right-nLat].tolist()
                field = [[all_real_data[sim][0][t][i] for i in np.asarray(coord_list)] for t in time_list]
                return field, len(time_list), len(coord_list)

def stack_bubbles(sim_selection, window_size, bubble_limit):
    bubbles, time_list, coord_list, average_bubble, average_bubble_error = [], [], [], [], []
    print('# simulations: ', len(sim_selection))
    for sim in sim_selection:
        a = cut_out_bubble(sim, window_size, bubble_limit)
        if a != None:
            bubbles.append(a[0]); time_list.append(a[1]); coord_list.append(a[2])
    print('# valid simulations: ', len(bubbles))

    rows = [ [ [ t for t in range(time_list[sim]) ] for sim in range(len(bubbles)) ] for coord in range(coord_list[-1])]
    for coord in range(coord_list[-1]):
        for sim in range(len(bubbles)):
            for t in range(time_list[sim]):
                rows[coord][sim][t] = bubbles[sim][t][coord]
    for coordinate in rows:
        xerr = np.nanstd(np.array(list(zip_longest(*coordinate)), dtype=float), axis=1, ddof=1)
        xerr = [x for x in xerr if str(x) != 'nan'][::-1]
        average_bubble_error.append(xerr)
        mean = np.nanmean(np.array(list(zip_longest(*coordinate)), dtype=float), axis=1)
        average_bubble.append(mean[:len(xerr)][::-1])
    return np.transpose(average_bubble, (1, 0)), np.transpose(average_bubble_error, (1, 0))

    deciman_places = 2

    y_list = [x for x in range(len(coleman_solution)) if truncateNum(coleman_solution[x], deciman_places) == truncateNum(2*np.pi, deciman_places)]
    coord_list = [x for x in range(len(coleman_solution)) if (x in x_list and x not in y_list)]
    for t in range(len(average_bubble)):
        a = [average_bubble[t][x] - coleman_solution[x] for x in coord_list]
        if min_sum > np.abs(sum(a)):
            min_sum = np.abs(sum(a))
            min_t = t
    return min_t, coleman_solution, min(x_list), max(x_list), min(y_list), max(y_list)

def plot_coleman_match(ab, window_size):
    average_bubble = ab[0]; average_bubble_error = ab[1]
    coleman_timeslice, coleman_solution, a, b, c, d = coleman_match(average_bubble, window_size)
    print(coleman_timeslice)
    
    solution = average_bubble[coleman_timeslice]
    solution_error = average_bubble_error[coleman_timeslice]
    difference = [coleman_solution[i] - solution[i] for i in range(len(coleman_solution))]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,4))
    im = ax.imshow(average_bubble, aspect='auto', interpolation='none', origin='lower')#, extent=[0, dx*len(average_bubble[0]), 0, dtout*len(average_bubble)])     
    clb = plt.colorbar(im, ax = ax)
    ax.set(xlabel = r'$x$', ylabel=r'$t$')
    ax.plot(np.arange(len(solution)), np.ones(len(solution))*coleman_timeslice, 'r-')
    plt.savefig(plots_file+'bubble_solution_'+suffix+'.png');
    plt.show()

    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,7))
    plt.errorbar(np.arange(len(solution)), solution, yerr = solution_error, color = 'k', marker='o', ms=1, ecolor = 'green', label = 'Average bubble')
    plt.plot(np.arange(len(coleman_solution)), coleman_solution, 'r-', linewidth=5.0, label = 'Coleman best fit at t = '+str(coleman_timeslice))
    plt.errorbar(np.arange(len(coleman_solution)), difference, yerr = solution_error, color = 'k', marker='o', ms=1, ecolor = 'yellow', label = 'Difference')
    plt.axvline(a, color = 'darkgray', ls = '--'); plt.axvline(b, color = 'darkgray', ls = '--')
    plt.axvline(c, color = 'darkgray', ls = '--'); plt.axvline(d, color = 'darkgray', ls = '--')
    plt.legend(); plt.grid()
    plt.savefig(plots_file+'bubble_profile_'+suffix+'.png');
    plt.show()
    return

Algorithm:¶

. Select values of phi between fix boundaries such that arrays have same length . Somehow keep their information about the time coordinate . Average those across all simulations of same type. That is a typical bubble signal

Other plots:

. Compute statistics: how many peaks of arbitrary height lead to decay. Or: out of the simulations that do not produce bubbles, how many peaks go above the arbitrary threshold? Think more about how to get this frequency: how to pinpoint which field maximum becomes center of bubble . Let time of bubble formation be when or around phi is at Vmax. That is how to detect bubble in simulation automatically. Some bubbles will appear before, others after. . Can do peak clustering correlations at said times, comparing against correlation at say, initial time, then compare to correlation in free field case
